The paper deals with the design and analysis of a Space-Time Block Code (STBC) for wireless communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and system and control theory (cs.SY). The use of adaptive modulation is also mentioned, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed code in terms of complexity and power efficiency, which are topics related to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
